Airline group Comair will temporarily suspend all its scheduled kulula.com and British Airways domestic flights in South Africa for three weeks as of Monday July 5, it  announced on Friday. This comes amid a fall in demand for air travel due to the Covid-19 third wave surge and alert Level 4 lockdown restrictions being implemented in the country. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
